really worked hard, there was no one else to work for you.

134
00:24:45,000 --> 00:24:48,000
Xalo, tu nizanî ka çima nav lê kirin Birc Abdul naha?
 
Uncle, do you know why they named it Burj Abdul now?

135
00:24:48,000 --> 00:24:55,000
Wa le.. nav lê kirine Borc Abdul go wextakî, zemaneki... ev
bidin mala Ebdal.
 
Well.. they named it Burj Abdul a long time ago, in the
past... this was given to the Abdal family.

136
00:24:55,000 --> 00:25:01,000
Go navî xwe Ebdal bûn. Bû Birc Abdul... Bi navê wî însanî
e...
 
They said their name was Abdal. So it became Burj Abdul...
It's from that person's name...

137
00:25:01,000 --> 00:25:08,000
Erê, we ye. Berê yane, ev însanî ne lî vî gundî ew avakir,
însan ew dî bûn.
 
Yes, that's how it is. In the past, I mean, these people
built this village, those people were the ones.

138
00:25:08,000 --> 00:25:12,000
Ew nuha ev gund wisa wekê ku sê sed mal hebûn.
 
Now this village has grown to about three hundred houses.

139
00:25:12,000 --> 00:25:15,000
Maşela.
 
Mashallah.

140
00:25:15,000 --> 00:25:21,000
Berê ne, em pêncî mal bûn, nuha buye wekî sê sed mal.. yanî
gelek ji hev.
 
In the past, we were fifty houses, now it has become about
three hundred houses.. meaning it expanded a lot.

141
00:25:21,000 --> 00:25:24,000
Mezin bîye.
 
It has grown.

142
00:25:24,000 --> 00:25:26,000
Erê mezin bu.
 
Yes it has grown.

143
00:25:26,000 --> 00:25:37,000
Saeta we xweş bî, dema îdê ye. Heci ziyaret ke, zewce
heseretî ce va ke ...
 
Have a good time, it is the holiday time. Let the pilgrims
visit, let the couples relieve their longings...

144
00:25:37,000 --> 00:25:40,000
Em... Xwedê emrê te dirêj pê da, Xwedê te neke ber destan
kes.
 
May... May God give you a long life, may God protect you
from needing anyone.

145
00:25:40,000 --> 00:25:48,000
Welle maşela bê yê de zehmet e, miletê gişt li Helebê ve
rawisti li gundê ... wek berê...
 
Indeed mashallah, otherwise it would be difficult, all the
people in Aleppo have stopped at the village... like
before...

146
00:25:48,000 --> 00:25:54,000
Wek berê nuha ez dikavim gundê, temaşeki miletê wî gundî gi
hatî... cem xwedanê xwe gundê xwe...
 
Like before, now I wander around the village, look at all
the people of this village who have come... to their owners
and their village...

147
00:25:54,000 --> 00:25:56,000
Berê jî we bî.
 
It used to be like this before too.

148
00:25:56,000 --> 00:25:59,000
Erê dîsan wek berê diftilî xweş debe, minteqe xweş dibe.
 
Yes, again returning to how it was before is nice, the
region becomes nice.

149
00:25:59,000 --> 00:26:08,000
Ez tim bi wan ra dibêm Xalo, di vîdyoyê de we dibêm. Ez de
bêm hûn bi dema têne, bas wana xo rûnin dest vala tîn.
 
I always tell them Uncle, I say it in the video. I say when
you come, you just sit there and come empty-handed.

150
00:26:08,000 --> 00:26:14,000
Faîdê min nakin! Welle, tê... milet wara projeyek vaki de...
 
You are of no use to me! Indeed, you come... people should
come and open a project...

151
00:26:14,000 --> 00:26:21,000
Saeta gundi xweş e... xwedê ew gundi... naha jî saeta
gundiya xweş e, naha ne wext e.
 
The village's times are nice... may God bless this
village... right now the villagers' times are nice, but now
is not the time.

152
00:26:21,000 --> 00:26:28,000
Aw fêdê bi bînê wî milet fêdê bide... Saeta gundî xweş o,
welle texsîrek nakin.
 
They should benefit, that nation should provide benefit...
The village's times are nice, indeed they don't hold back.

153
00:26:28,000 --> 00:26:33,000
Her yek wê meşrokek xwe veke da gundê xwe de da bajariyê xwe
de.. saeta gundiyên xweş e..
 
Each one should open their own project in their village and
in their city.. the villagers' times are nice..

154
00:26:33,000 --> 00:26:41,000
Bas tim hewşa me kin.. hewş kirin e, awur Zeytuna biki awi
aw ceda .. na wa genda ji bo jer de batr bi ye.
 
But don't just build courtyards.. they build courtyards, go
plant olives... no, this village has become better than the
city.

155
00:26:41,000 --> 00:26:46,000
Genda jî.. hew denda ardî dibe bi sed dolarî ($100), sed
dolar mêtir.
 
Even the village.. the price of land here has become a
hundred dollars, a hundred dollars per meter.

156
00:26:46,000 --> 00:26:49,000
Mêtir mêtir?
 
A meter?

157
00:26:49,000 --> 00:26:57,000
Naha miterê cemêrek he mi derbçine... min xwest e dî ta zewt
turbî e... ew lora pêncî dî.
 
Now if a man has a meter and sells it to me... I wanted to
buy a piece of soil... it was fifty liras.

158
00:26:57,000 --> 00:27:05,000
Gundîyekî ew bi pêncî na xirê ... yew mêtir li wîr bî... Ew
e Ewrûpa belkî metrek nebî sed dolar e ...
 
A villager wouldn't buy it for fifty... one meter there...
In Europe maybe a meter isn't even a hundred dollars...

159
00:27:05,000 --> 00:27:11,000
E Ewrûpa ahsen e. Ewrûpa ehsenî hewş bikiri... yane yek
kîbar, bes yek xwa bikir..
 
Well, Europe is better. It is better to buy a courtyard in
Europe... meaning a nice one, just buy one for yourself..

160
00:27:11,000 --> 00:27:18,000
Yanî pêncî hezar ti dî bikiri li Ewrûpa... Xwazê gund de ha
ye... welle heye .. ev ji pêncî hezar dolara..
 
Meaning you would buy it for fifty thousand in Europe... I
wish there was one in the village... indeed there is.. this
is fifty thousand dollars too..

161
00:27:18,000 --> 00:27:22,000
Erê paşî ha zeytunê ne ardî ev e dî de.
 
Yes, and later on there are the olives and the land provides
as well.

162
00:27:22,000 --> 00:27:29,000
Vê gavê ti keri ev biçi te kî ye sed... te wî bi penci ji
têkive sed ... ci wê ram... zahmet a wa.
 
Now if you try to make it a hundred... if you try to turn
fifty into a hundred... what will happen... it's difficult.

163
00:27:29,000 --> 00:27:36,000
Ez ev daxwa we ser teker dî kî re. Dili mi xede gazî me, ev
carenî, nacive bi der da ...
 
I will leave this request repeatedly for you. My heart calls
for us, this time, don't stay outside...

164
00:27:36,000 --> 00:27:41,000
Mi bi vi sed hezar, bi çar hezar dolar e madbex û hammam bas
i ye..
 
I wouldn't do a hundred thousand, a kitchen and a bathroom
for four thousand dollars is enough for me..

165
00:27:41,000 --> 00:27:43,000
Erê welle bas î ye.
 
Yes, indeed it's enough.

166
00:27:43,000 --> 00:27:49,000
Xwedê emrê gi derêj de, xwedê we nî ke ber destan. Bay bay
ka! Qeçika xwa ra bay bay ka!
 
May God give you all a long life, may God protect you from
needing others. Say bye bye! Say bye bye to your girl!

167
00:27:49,000 --> 00:27:53,000
Bay bay bay... we gî ya ra.
 
Bye bye bye... to all of you.

168
00:27:53,000 --> 00:27:58,000
Weren ha wira dîna, ah... Weren Rênas ra dîna, çew ya Rênas
we?
 
Come look there, ah... Come look at Renas, how is your
Renas?

169
00:27:58,000 --> 00:27:59,000
Xweş.
 
Good.

170
00:27:59,000 --> 00:28:06,000
Ma te ra rohet in ane ham... em vegîya silav di kan a... em
cavên gî re xweş dî kan, wela mi bi rîya we ki r i ye.
 
Are you comfortable... we send greetings to all of you... we
happily greet you all, indeed I have missed you.

171
00:28:06,000 --> 00:28:12,000
Axir cavên we, em vî bidin welle wê wa na a... Ca ew pisa we
ra ma devî de dî bin e...
 
Look at your eyes, if we give this, well it will be... Just
let your son see it on his face...

172
00:28:12,000 --> 00:28:19,000
We kû a dî wî w e na, em tişt nî n i na te ne... em tiştê na
dî n i w va va w e b i t î t e.
 
We are fine there, we don't lack anything here... we just
watch things here like that.

173
00:28:19,000 --> 00:28:26,000
Wela silava min qîzika mi ra, ew qeçika mi ye, em çavên gî
wara silav diki maç diki.. e Rênas o ...
 
Indeed my greetings to my daughter, my little girl, we greet
everyone and kiss their eyes.. oh Renas...

174
00:28:26,000 --> 00:28:34,000
E abo awla. wî silava min giya ra hene, wem cavên wa gî de
rahat in a, a em silav di k in.
 
Oh my first son. I have greetings for all of them, may they
be comfortable, we send our greetings.

175
00:28:34,000 --> 00:28:41,000
Bes dî dî re, wa gar a k î te şe t i te g e re ke me de.
 
But enough of this, you should return to us sometime.

176
00:28:41,000 --> 00:28:47,000
Xwedê saeta we xweş bike. Ew em ne dex destî bextê, xwedê we
saeta we. Bay bay ka!
 
May God make your times pleasant. May your hands and
fortunes be blessed, may God bless your times. Say bye bye!

177
00:28:47,000 --> 00:28:49,000
Bay bay!
 
Bye bye!

178
00:28:49,000 --> 00:28:58,000
Weren e w na wa bi n i n ... Wela teyare ya we fêhm nedar
in.. Weren gundî dî ne... tefeta carkî dî...
 
Come and see this... Well, they don't understand your
airplanes.. Come see the village... return once more...

179
00:28:58,000 --> 00:29:18,000
Rênas aw qiza xwe wî ne ... te ne ev am gî ... di wî r ...
 
Renas and his daughter are not coming... they are not...
they are far...

180
00:31:48,000 --> 00:31:52,000
Erê xwişk û birayên ezîz, ev jî mala bavê te ye, em tê re
derbas bin.
 
Yes dear brothers and sisters, this is also your father's
house, let's pass through it.

181
00:31:52,000 --> 00:31:56,000
Bes kes tê de nîne, te digot me çû kilît wêna nînin.
 
But there is no one inside, you said we went and they didn't
have the key.

182
00:31:56,000 --> 00:32:00,000
Ji aliyê te da tiştê şewitî kiribû rî.
 
On your side, you had burned the things.

183
00:32:00,000 --> 00:32:06,000
Ev e. Em havliya mala me bi we didin gerandin ha.
 
This is it. We are showing you around the courtyard of our
house.

184
00:32:06,000 --> 00:32:20,000
Teba em hundirê wê jî bidin naskirin.
 
Now let's introduce its inside as well.

185
00:32:20,000 --> 00:32:24,000
Qey te par di vir re, li çiyê serxwe xeniye.
 
Did you perhaps through here last year, choke on the
mountain yourself.

186
00:32:24,000 --> 00:32:32,000
Oh, çiko çelek tê de wekî rine. Wî...
 
Oh, because cows are like sitting inside. Wow...

187
00:32:32,000 --> 00:32:35,000
Wileh havşa we, gîyayê wê mezin e, çend ode ne.
 
By God your courtyard, its grass is big, how many rooms are
there.

188
00:32:35,000 --> 00:32:40,000
Yek li vir e, yek li vir e, yek li vir e, yek li vir e.
 
One is here, one is here, one is here, one is here.

189
00:32:40,000 --> 00:32:45,000
Hemû girtî ne, kilît nîne ha.
 
They are all closed, there is no key here.

190
00:32:45,000 --> 00:32:48,000
Rê nava du salan vir de rahat rûniştiye.
 
The road inside has been sitting comfortably here for two
years.

191
00:32:48,000 --> 00:32:53,000
Feqîre, ava ancax korakek lê heye na? Ev metbex e?
 
Poor thing, this barely has a blind spot, no? Is this the
kitchen?

192
00:32:53,000 --> 00:32:54,000
Qap e na.
 
It's the door, no.

193
00:32:54,000 --> 00:33:00,000
Qap e wa ye. Deriyê dîwar li we da ketiye.
 
That is the door. The wall door has fallen on you.

194
00:33:00,000 --> 00:33:01,000
Dîwarê dorê aliyê kû derê ye?
 
Which side is the surrounding wall?

195
00:33:01,000 --> 00:33:04,000
Dîwarê dorê yê hundir e.
 
The surrounding wall is the inside one.

196
00:33:04,000 --> 00:33:09,000
Ev havşa wê ye.
 
This is its courtyard.

197
00:33:09,000 --> 00:33:13,000
Darên wê piçûk in, xizmetê naxwazin na?
 
Its trees are small, they don't want service, no?

198
00:33:13,000 --> 00:33:16,000
Av nîne, ji ber wê dîsa tiştek hişk nabe.
 
There is no water, that's why nothing will dry again.

199
00:33:16,000 --> 00:33:18,000
Bes şikestî dane.
 
They are just broken.

200
00:33:18,000 --> 00:33:24,000
Ev e havşa wê ye. Navê wê çi bû hişk bûye.
 
This is its courtyard. Whatever its name was has dried up.

201
00:33:24,000 --> 00:33:26,000
Bi Xwedê we jî hişk bûye.
 
By God, you too have dried up.

202
00:33:26,000 --> 00:33:31,000
Mirov yek tê de rabe, rûnê, xizmet bike...
 
If someone gets up, sits in it, provides service...

203
00:33:31,000 --> 00:33:38,000
Dîsa wekî berê vedibe.
 
It will open up again like before.

204
00:33:38,000 --> 00:33:43,000
Maşallah.
 
Mashallah.

205
00:33:43,000 --> 00:33:48,000
Dîwar qelişî ye.
 
The wall is cracked.

206
00:33:48,000 --> 00:33:51,000
Em biçin ser xaniyê we.
 
Let's go onto your roof.

207
00:33:51,000 --> 00:33:58,000
Ser xaniyê gundiyên we fireh e hê.
 
The roof of your villagers is wide, hey.

208
00:33:58,000 --> 00:34:09,000
Maşallah, ev jî cîranên te ne. Cîranên te wan e.
 
Mashallah, these are also your neighbors. Those are your
neighbors.

209
00:34:09,000 --> 00:34:14,000
Vê dinê ez li dûr digerim, ew jî sariyê ne.
 
In this world I walk far, they are also cold.

210
00:34:14,000 --> 00:34:19,000
Min go darê navê wê li vir heye, dît te?
 
I said there is a tree with its name here, did you see?

211
00:34:19,000 --> 00:34:23,000
Min go em darê navê wê bibînin, mala meta te li gundê din e.
 
I said let's see its named tree, your aunt's house is in the
other village.

212
00:34:23,000 --> 00:34:31,000
Çi hewşekî mezin e maşallah, tiştine rind danîne. Xwedê
rizkê wan zêde bike.
 
What a big courtyard mashallah, they've placed beautiful
things. May God increase their sustenance.

213
00:34:31,000 --> 00:34:43,000
Biragêlî ev çiyê we ye... giya e.
 
Brother what is this of yours... it is grass.

214
00:34:43,000 --> 00:34:53,000
Lênêre, ji her yekî re yek heye. Ne wisa?
 
Look, there is one for everyone. Isn't that so?

215
00:34:53,000 --> 00:35:00,000
Hemberî wê hewşê, ji kevir û partan digirin ji xwe re
derdixin.
 
Opposite that courtyard, they take it from stones and parts
and take it out for themselves.

216
00:35:00,000 --> 00:35:13,000
Min go hewşan qat bi qat digirin, çêdikin.
 
I said they take courtyards level by level and build them.

217
00:35:13,000 --> 00:35:18,000
Bêguman, kes ne nêzîkê kilît e.
 
Of course, no one is close to the key.

218
00:35:18,000 --> 00:35:24,000
Hewş bi giştî, heger kes tê de rûnenê, bi giştî xera dibe.
 
The courtyard in general, if no one sits in it, generally
gets ruined.

219
00:35:24,000 --> 00:35:32,000
Çiqas jî mirov pak bike, nîşan bide, heger tu tê de
rûneniştî, hefteyekê ji malê derkeve û here. Tu yê bibînî ew
der çawa xera dibe na?
 
No matter how much one cleans it, shows it, if you don't sit
in it, leave the house for a week and go. You will see how
that place gets ruined, right?

220
00:35:32,000 --> 00:35:35,000
Haşa, paşê ew tişt jî xerab dibe.
 
God forbid, then that thing also gets ruined.

221
00:35:35,000 --> 00:35:55,000
Mala me ye, ma kesek tê de tune, çima erzan e weha. Yallah
em li vir temam bikin.
 
It's our house, is there no one in it, why is it cheap like
this. Yallah let's finish here.

222
00:37:00,000 --> 00:37:04,000
Xwişka min, em jî li ber deriyê mala hanê ne, em dê di vir
re derbas bin.
 
My sister, we are also at the door of that house, we will
pass through here.

223
00:37:04,000 --> 00:37:13,000
Ev e mala nîna te ye. Maşallah, hewşa wê fireh e.
 
This is your grandmother's house. Mashallah, its courtyard
is wide.

224
00:37:13,000 --> 00:37:33,000
Ev e, hewşa mala nîna te ye.
 
This is it, the courtyard of your grandmother's house.

225
00:37:44,000 --> 00:38:04,000
Reş û qirêj dinya genî kir.
 
Black and dirt made the world stink.

226
00:38:26,000 --> 00:38:46,000
Welleh ev hewş weke yên bajarane ye.
 
By God, this courtyard is like those of the cities.

227
00:39:28,000 --> 00:39:30,000
Ew a jor da ne ya te ye, ne?
 
That one from above is not yours, right?

228
00:39:30,000 --> 00:39:33,000
Na, a jor da yên wan e. A na...
 
No, the one from above is theirs. This no...

229
00:39:33,000 --> 00:39:36,000
Bes hatiye kêlekê, te girtiye ser xwe derbas dibî.
 
It just came to the side, you took it upon yourself to pass.

230
00:39:36,000 --> 00:39:38,000
Tê de derketin me ew dît.
 
Going out in it, we saw it.

231
00:39:38,000 --> 00:39:43,000
Kî ketiye hundir te tiştek nedît? Min got "Bextê we me, min
tiştek nekiriye."
 
Whoever entered inside, didn't you see anything? I said "I
swear to you, I didn't do anything."

232
00:39:43,000 --> 00:39:48,000
Mala dinê derket holê em çûn hundir. Tiştekî wisa nîne, wê
da binî tê dayîn.
 
The other house appeared, we went inside. There is no such
thing, it's given down there.

233
00:39:48,000 --> 00:39:54,000
Maşallah çend qayîm û xweş e.
 
Mashallah, how sturdy and beautiful it is.

234
00:39:54,000 --> 00:40:00,000
Xaniyê wan weha xweş in, erê.
 
Their houses are beautiful like this, yes.

235
00:40:00,000 --> 00:40:20,000
Mêzeke gund mezin e, da ela yeha kem min we da fêmkirin.
 
Look the village is big, so I will make you understand.

236
00:40:39,000 --> 00:40:44,000
Ev jî tirbeya vê gundî ne, Xwedê rehma xwe lê ke, cihê
giyanê wî cenet be.
 
These are also the tombs of this village, may God have mercy
on him, may his soul's place be heaven.

237
00:40:44,000 --> 00:40:46,000
Rê.
 
Road.

238
00:40:46,000 --> 00:40:48,000
Maşallah we re pir in ha.
 
Mashallah, come, there are a lot here.

239
00:40:48,000 --> 00:40:54,000
Hey, ho ho, pir in ha.
 
Hey, ho ho, there are a lot.

240
00:40:54,000 --> 00:41:14,000
Hey gund mezin e ha.
 
Hey, the village is big.

241
00:41:36,000 --> 00:41:56,000
Makîne bi soraat dajo di vir ra.
 
The car is driving fast through here.

242
00:42:25,000 --> 00:42:27,000
Newrozek dît min...
 
I saw a Newroz...

243
00:42:27,000 --> 00:42:28,000
Na min qe rojek wisa nedî.
 
No, I never saw a day like this.

244
00:42:28,000 --> 00:42:48,000
Bira.
 
Brother.

245
00:42:55,000 --> 00:43:00,000
Erê hevalno, ev hewşên malên xaltîka min in, xalî mane, erê.
 
Yes friends, these are the courtyards of my aunt's houses,
they have remained empty, yes.

246
00:43:00,000 --> 00:43:05,000
Maşallah vira pir rind e.
 
Mashallah here is very nice.

247
00:43:05,000 --> 00:43:08,000
Hey kêleka, ku em di vira ra herin.
 
Hey to the side, let's go through here.

248
00:43:08,000 --> 00:43:11,000
Werin, werin ev alî werin.
 
Come, come to this side.

249
00:43:11,000 --> 00:43:16,000
Ehê, ehê.
 
Aha, aha.

250
00:43:16,000 --> 00:43:20,000
Çi bînayeke xweş e, bînayeke xweş e.
 
What a nice building, it's a nice building.

251
00:43:20,000 --> 00:43:24,000
Xaltîk jî li vir e, dolme çêdike. Dolme ne, ne?
 
Aunt is here too, making dolmas. They are dolmas, right?

252
00:43:24,000 --> 00:43:30,000
Eşyayê wê, ew camê wê qeşqeyên xwe jî avêtin e. E... Ez pir
rûnenim, lê bişewitin.
 
Her things, her glass, she has also thrown her scraps. Uh...
I won't sit much, otherwise they will burn.

253
00:43:30,000 --> 00:43:32,000
Ew hêşin in.
 
They are fresh.

254
00:43:32,000 --> 00:43:43,000
Ah, hêşin in na? Em pir qeyr nekin, belkî em biqerisin.
 
Ah, they are fresh no? We shouldn't talk much, maybe we will
freeze.

255
00:43:43,000 --> 00:43:52,000
Saet ke, hewşê maro çiqas fireh bin, wexte sarin da maro bi
hesreta xwe dibîne.
 
Look, how wide the snake's courtyard is, in the cold time
the snake sees it with longing.

256
00:43:52,000 --> 00:44:10,000
Ev hewşê mala dadiya min e Lêylû, ma li vir daliya Lêylû.
Dadiya min...
 
This is the courtyard of my mother's house Leylu, here is
the house of Leylu. My mother...

257
00:44:10,000 --> 00:44:16,000
Maro li xerîbiyê be, gundên maro, bajarên maro, xetwe-xetwe
tê bîra maro.
 
For us in exile, our villages, our cities, step by step come
to our minds.

258
